## Permitted Purpose

Subject to the Excluded Purpose section below, which controls over this section
in the event of any conflict, each of the following is a Permitted Purpose:

(a) **Personal Use.** Personal use for research, experiment, study, private
    entertainment, hobby projects, or amateur pursuits, in each case without any
    anticipated commercial application and without use on any Operational System
    or processing of any Live Data.

(b) **Research, Classroom Instruction, and Software Verification.** Academic or
    scientific research, Classroom Instruction, and Software Verification,
    provided that ALL such use occurs exclusively on one or more Test or Research
    Systems and does not occur on any Operational System and does not process,
    ingest, monitor, or analyze any Live Data.

For clarity, the permissions in this section apply only while every condition of
the applicable definition (including the Test or Research System conditions in
the Definitions section) is satisfied. Use that begins as a Permitted Purpose but
later fails any such condition ceases to be licensed under these terms at the time
of that failure and requires a separate commercial license.

## Excluded Purpose (Requires a Commercial License)

Notwithstanding the Permitted Purpose section or any other grant in these terms,
and regardless of whether the user is an individual, a for-profit entity, or any
charitable, educational, public-research, public-safety, public-health,
environmental, or governmental organization, the following are NOT permitted
under this license and require a separate written commercial license from the
licensor:

(1) Use of the software for operational security monitoring, threat detection,
    digital forensics, incident response, auditing, or investigation that is
    performed to conduct, support, protect, defend, or investigate the systems,
    networks, endpoints, data, services, personnel, or operations of any
    organization, including the user's own institution;

(2) Any use of the software on, or to monitor, an Operational System;

(3) Any use of the software that stores, processes, ingests, transmits, monitors,
    or analyzes Live Data; and

(4) Any use of the software to conduct, fulfill, or otherwise complete
    Institutional Operations.

The nonprofit, educational, governmental, or charitable status of an organization,
and the source of its funding, do not make an Excluded Purpose permitted.

## Security Operations (Clarification)

Research, experimentation, or testing carried out by a security operations center
("SOC") or equivalent security function may itself be a normal function of that
SOC. Such research, experimentation, or testing is a Permitted Purpose ONLY when
all of the following are true: (i) it is conducted exclusively on Test or Research
Systems; (ii) it is not conducted on, and does not monitor, any Operational System
or any system used for live or normal operations; (iii) it does not process Live
Data; and (iv) it satisfies the objective/deadline and teardown conditions in the
definition of "Test or Research System." Any use of the software by a SOC or
security function to monitor, defend, investigate, or respond on or for the
organization's live or operational systems is an Excluded Purpose and requires a
commercial license.

