## Definitions

The **licensor** is the individual or entity offering these terms, and the
**software** is the software the licensor makes available under these terms.

**You** refers to the individual or entity agreeing to these terms.

**Your company** is any legal entity, sole proprietorship, or other kind of
organization that you work for, plus all organizations that have control over,
are under the control of, or are under common control with that organization.
**Control** means ownership of substantially all the assets of an entity, or the
power to direct its management and policies by vote, contract, or otherwise.
Control can be direct or indirect.

**Your licenses** are all the licenses granted to you for the software under
these terms.

**Use** means anything you do with the software requiring one of your licenses.

**Classroom Instruction** means the delivery of educational instruction in the
form of live in-person courses, synchronous virtual courses, or asynchronous
virtual courses.

**Institutional Operations** means the functions required to conduct, fulfill, or
otherwise complete the normal operations of an institution or organization,
including the operation, administration, security, and defense of the systems,
networks, and data used to carry out those functions.

**Operational System** means any physical or virtual system, device, endpoint,
network, or service that is used (in whole or in part) to conduct, fulfill, or
otherwise complete Institutional Operations, or that stores, processes, or
transmits Live Data. Any system used for live or normal operations is an
Operational System.

**Live Data** means any data that originates from, is collected by, or is
processed by an Operational System in the course of Institutional Operations,
including production data and any data concerning real persons, systems, or
events. Live Data does not include synthetic, fabricated, sample, or other data
created solely for research, Classroom Instruction, or Software Verification.

**Software Verification** means functional evaluation, validation, compatibility
testing, or quality assurance of the software itself, conducted to confirm how
the software behaves, and not deployed for the monitoring, defense, or
investigation of any Operational System or Live Data.

**Test or Research System** means a physical or virtual system deployed
specifically and solely for research, Classroom Instruction, or Software
Verification, that meets ALL of the following conditions:

  (i)   it is not an Operational System and is not used for any live or normal
        operations of any institution or organization;

  (ii)  it does not store, process, ingest, transmit, monitor, or analyze any
        Live Data;

  (iii) it is established for a specific, documented research, instructional, or
        verification objective and/or under a defined deadline or time period;
        and

  (iv)  it is decommissioned and torn down upon completion of the applicable
        research, Classroom Instruction, or Software Verification objective or
        upon expiration of the applicable deadline or time period, whichever
        occurs first.

